NMX Server REST API

API and SDK Documentation

Version: v2.3
This document describes the REST API and resources provided by NMX for integration with external applications.

Cards

cardsGetCard

Get card by ID

Get card details by id


/api/Topology/v2/Cards/{id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET "https://127.0.0.1/api/Topology/v2/Cards/{id}"

import io.swagger.client.model.*;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CardsApi apiInstance = new CardsApi();
        UUID id = ; // UUID | Card ID
        try {
            Card result = apiInstance.cardsGetCard(id);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CardsApi#cardsGetCard");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

CardsApi *apiInstance = [[CardsApi alloc] init];

// Get card by ID
[apiInstance cardsGetCardWith:id
              completionHandler: ^(Card output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};

Devices

devicesGetAllDevices

Get all devices

Get all devices present on NMX server


/api/Topology/v2/Devices

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET "https://127.0.0.1/api/Topology/v2/Devices?networkGroupId=&deviceName=&physicalDeviceOnly=&connectedDeviceOnly=&chassisOnly=&switchOnly="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.DevicesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class DevicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        DevicesApi apiInstance = new DevicesApi();
        String networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example; // String | Optional filter to get device by network group id
        String deviceName = deviceName_example; // String | Optional filter to get device by name, comparison is using ignore case.
        Boolean physicalDeviceOnly = true; // Boolean | Optional filter to get physical devices only
        Boolean connectedDeviceOnly = true; // Boolean | Option filter to return only connected devices
        Boolean chassisOnly = true; // Boolean | Option filter to return chassis info only without cards and ports
        Boolean switchOnly = true; // Boolean | Optional filter to get switches only
        try {
            array[Device] result = apiInstance.devicesGetAllDevices(networkGroupId, deviceName, physicalDeviceOnly, connectedDeviceOnly, chassisOnly, switchOnly);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DevicesApi#devicesGetAllDevices");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.DevicesApi;

public class DevicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        DevicesApi apiInstance = new DevicesApi();
        String networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example; // String | Optional filter to get device by network group id
        String deviceName = deviceName_example; // String | Optional filter to get device by name, comparison is using ignore case.
        Boolean physicalDeviceOnly = true; // Boolean | Optional filter to get physical devices only
        Boolean connectedDeviceOnly = true; // Boolean | Option filter to return only connected devices
        Boolean chassisOnly = true; // Boolean | Option filter to return chassis info only without cards and ports
        Boolean switchOnly = true; // Boolean | Optional filter to get switches only
        try {
            array[Device] result = apiInstance.devicesGetAllDevices(networkGroupId, deviceName, physicalDeviceOnly, connectedDeviceOnly, chassisOnly, switchOnly);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DevicesApi#devicesGetAllDevices");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
String *networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example; // Optional filter to get device by network group id (optional)
String *deviceName = deviceName_example; // Optional filter to get device by name, comparison is using ignore case. (optional)
Boolean *physicalDeviceOnly = true; // Optional filter to get physical devices only (optional)
Boolean *connectedDeviceOnly = true; // Option filter to return only connected devices (optional)
Boolean *chassisOnly = true; // Option filter to return chassis info only without cards and ports (optional)
Boolean *switchOnly = true; // Optional filter to get switches only (optional)

DevicesApi *apiInstance = [[DevicesApi alloc] init];

// Get all devices
[apiInstance devicesGetAllDevicesWith:networkGroupId
    deviceName:deviceName
    physicalDeviceOnly:physicalDeviceOnly
    connectedDeviceOnly:connectedDeviceOnly
    chassisOnly:chassisOnly
    switchOnly:switchOnly
              completionHandler: ^(array[Device] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.DevicesApi()

var opts = { 
  'networkGroupId': networkGroupId_example, // {String} Optional filter to get device by network group id
  'deviceName': deviceName_example, // {String} Optional filter to get device by name, comparison is using ignore case.
  'physicalDeviceOnly': true, // {Boolean} Optional filter to get physical devices only
  'connectedDeviceOnly': true, // {Boolean} Option filter to return only connected devices
  'chassisOnly': true, // {Boolean} Option filter to return chassis info only without cards and ports
  'switchOnly': true // {Boolean} Optional filter to get switches only
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.devicesGetAllDevices(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class devicesGetAllDevicesExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            var apiInstance = new DevicesApi();
            var networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example;  // String | Optional filter to get device by network group id (optional) 
            var deviceName = deviceName_example;  // String | Optional filter to get device by name, comparison is using ignore case. (optional) 
            var physicalDeviceOnly = true;  // Boolean | Optional filter to get physical devices only (optional) 
            var connectedDeviceOnly = true;  // Boolean | Option filter to return only connected devices (optional) 
            var chassisOnly = true;  // Boolean | Option filter to return chassis info only without cards and ports (optional) 
            var switchOnly = true;  // Boolean | Optional filter to get switches only (optional) 

            try
            {
                // Get all devices
                array[Device] result = apiInstance.devicesGetAllDevices(networkGroupId, deviceName, physicalDeviceOnly, connectedDeviceOnly, chassisOnly, switchOnly);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling DevicesApi.devicesGetAllDevices: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

my $deviceName = deviceName_example; # String | Optional filter to get device by name, comparison is using ignore case.
my $physicalDeviceOnly = true; # Boolean | Optional filter to get physical devices only
my $connectedDeviceOnly = true; # Boolean | Option filter to return only connected devices
my $chassisOnly = true; # Boolean | Option filter to return chassis info only without cards and ports
my $switchOnly = true; # Boolean | Optional filter to get switches only

eval { 
    my $result = $api_instance->devicesGetAllDevices(networkGroupId => $networkGroupId, deviceName => $deviceName, physicalDeviceOnly => $physicalDeviceOnly, connectedDeviceOnly => $connectedDeviceOnly, chassisOnly => $chassisOnly, switchOnly => $switchOnly);
    print Dumper($result);
};
if ($@) {
    warn "Exception when calling DevicesApi->devicesGetAllDevices: $@\n";
}
from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import swagger_client
from swagger_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# create an instance of the API class
api_instance = swagger_client.DevicesApi()
networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example # String | Optional filter to get device by network group id (optional)
deviceName = deviceName_example # String | Optional filter to get device by name, comparison is using ignore case. (optional)
physicalDeviceOnly = true # Boolean | Optional filter to get physical devices only (optional)
connectedDeviceOnly = true # Boolean | Option filter to return only connected devices (optional)
chassisOnly = true # Boolean | Option filter to return chassis info only without cards and ports (optional)
switchOnly = true # Boolean | Optional filter to get switches only (optional)

try: 
    # Get all devices
    api_response = api_instance.devices_get_all_devices(networkGroupId=networkGroupId, deviceName=deviceName, physicalDeviceOnly=physicalDeviceOnly, connectedDeviceOnly=connectedDeviceOnly, chassisOnly=chassisOnly, switchOnly=switchOnly)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling DevicesApi->devicesGetAllDevices: %s\n" % e)

import io.swagger.client.*;

import io.swagger.client.model.*;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class DevicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        DevicesApi apiInstance = new DevicesApi();
        array[UUID] deviceIdList = ; // array[UUID] | List of physical device IDs, JSON array. (Note: Duplicate IDs and IDs in invalid format will be ignored.)
        Boolean partial = true; // Boolean | If 'Partial' is set to 'true', API will only fetch ID, Name, ServiceNumber and PCRPid fields for every service. 
            If 'Partial' is set to 'false', API will fetch full details for every service. Default: 'true'
        try {
            array[OutputServiceConfig] result = apiInstance.devicesGetDeviceServiceListBulk(deviceIdList, partial);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DevicesApi#devicesGetDeviceServiceListBulk");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.DevicesApi;

public class DevicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        DevicesApi apiInstance = new DevicesApi();
        array[UUID] deviceIdList = ; // array[UUID] | List of physical device IDs, JSON array. (Note: Duplicate IDs and IDs in invalid format will be ignored.)
        Boolean partial = true; // Boolean | If 'Partial' is set to 'true', API will only fetch ID, Name, ServiceNumber and PCRPid fields for every service. 
            If 'Partial' is set to 'false', API will fetch full details for every service. Default: 'true'
        try {
            array[OutputServiceConfig] result = apiInstance.devicesGetDeviceServiceListBulk(deviceIdList, partial);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DevicesApi#devicesGetDeviceServiceListBulk");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
array[UUID] *deviceIdList = ; // List of physical device IDs, JSON array. (Note: Duplicate IDs and IDs in invalid format will be ignored.)
Boolean *partial = true; // If 'Partial' is set to 'true', API will only fetch ID, Name, ServiceNumber and PCRPid fields for every service. 
            If 'Partial' is set to 'false', API will fetch full details for every service. Default: 'true' (optional)

// Get provisioned services on devices

    partial:partial
              completionHandler: ^(array[OutputServiceConfig] output, NSError* error) {

                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }

devicesPutDevice

Update Device by ID

Update device properties identified by its object id. Switch devices are not supported in this API.


/api/Topology/v2/Devices/{id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#

  • Python

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.DevicesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class DevicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        DevicesApi apiInstance = new DevicesApi();
        UUID id = ; // UUID | Device object id
        UpdateDeviceInfo updateDeviceInfo = ; // UpdateDeviceInfo | Device info to be updated
        try {
            UpdateDeviceInfo result = apiInstance.devicesPutDevice(id, updateDeviceInfo);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DevicesApi#devicesPutDevice");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        DevicesApi apiInstance = new DevicesApi();
        UUID id = ; // UUID | Master device ID
        UpdateBackupDevice backupDevice = ; // UpdateBackupDevice | Device to update
        Boolean mute = true; // Boolean | Mirror Device output to be muted or not
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.devicesPutMirrorToDevice(id, backupDevice, mute);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DevicesApi#devicesPutMirrorToDevice");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

import io.swagger.client.api.DevicesApi;

public class DevicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        DevicesApi apiInstance = new DevicesApi();
        UUID id = ; // UUID | Master device ID
        UpdateBackupDevice backupDevice = ; // UpdateBackupDevice | Device to update
        Boolean mute = true; // Boolean | Mirror Device output to be muted or not
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.devicesPutMirrorToDevice(id, backupDevice, mute);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DevicesApi#devicesPutMirrorToDevice");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

UUID *id = ; // Master device ID
UpdateBackupDevice *backupDevice = ; // Device to update
Boolean *mute = true; // Mirror Device output to be muted or not (optional)

DevicesApi *apiInstance = [[DevicesApi alloc] init];

// Add Mirror on backup device by ID
[apiInstance devicesPutMirrorToDeviceWith:id
    backupDevice:backupDevice
    mute:mute
              completionHandler: ^(Object output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.DevicesApi()

var id = ; // {UUID} Master device ID

var backupDevice = ; // {UpdateBackupDevice} Device to update

var opts = { 
  'mute': true // {Boolean} Mirror Device output to be muted or not
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.devicesPutMirrorToDevice(id, backupDevice, opts, callback);

devicesUpdateSwitchPortMapping

Update SwitchPort Mapping Information

Map the logical switch ports to physical ports, see the limitations below: 1. Switch port mapping is not available for stub switches 2. Device mapping mode should be Port Level Mapping


/api/Topology/v2/Devices/{id}/SwitchPortMapping

  • Android

        String startTime = startTime_example; // String | The optional oldest Assert Time for Alarms
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | The maximum number of alarms present in the response, should be a positive number greater than 0 (default=100, Max=1000)
        Integer offset = 56; // Integer | Number of Alarm records to skip, should be a positive number. (default=0)

    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling PortsApi->portsGetPort: %s\n" % e)

portsPutPort

Update IP settings of a Port by its Object ID

Update port operation is supported for following devices: 1. ProStream X 2. Electra XOS 3. Electra X Note: For ProStream X, properties of management port cannot be updated.


/api/Topology/v2/Ports/{id}

        String networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example; // String | Filter to get all ECMG in a NetworkGroup
        String name = name_example; // String | Filter to get ECMG by name
        try {
            array[ECMGConfiguration] result = apiInstance.scramblingGetAllECMGConfiguration(networkGroupId, name);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ScramblingApi#scramblingGetAllECMGConfiguration");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    name:name

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ScramblingApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ScramblingApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        ScramblingApi apiInstance = new ScramblingApi();
        UUID outputTransportId = ; // UUID | Object ID of output transport
        try {
            array[EMMData] result = apiInstance.scramblingGetAllEMMByOutputTs(outputTransportId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ScramblingApi#scramblingGetAllEMMByOutputTs");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

UUID *outputTransportId = ; // Object ID of output transport

ScramblingApi *apiInstance = [[ScramblingApi alloc] init];

// Get all EMM streams present in a output transport
[apiInstance scramblingGetAllEMMByOutputTsWith:outputTransportId
              completionHandler: ^(array[EMMData] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.ScramblingApi()

var outputTransportId = ; // {UUID} Object ID of output transport


var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.scramblingGetAllEMMByOutputTs(outputTransportId, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class scramblingGetAllEMMByOutputTsExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            var apiInstance = new ScramblingApi();
            var outputTransportId = new UUID(); // UUID | Object ID of output transport

            try
            {
                // Get all EMM streams present in a output transport
                array[EMMData] result = apiInstance.scramblingGetAllEMMByOutputTs(outputTransportId);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ScramblingApi.scramblingGetAllEMMByOutputTs: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

};

    warn "Exception when calling ScramblingApi->scramblingGetAllEMMByOutputTs: $@\n";
}

scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration

Get all EMMG by filter criteria


/api/Scrambling/v2/EMMG

curl -X GET "https://127.0.0.1/api/Scrambling/v2/EMMG?networkGroupId=&name="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ScramblingApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ScramblingApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        ScramblingApi apiInstance = new ScramblingApi();
        String networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example; // String | Filter to get all EMMG in a NetworkGroup
        String name = name_example; // String | Filter to get EMMG by name
        try {
            array[EMMGConfiguration] result = apiInstance.scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration(networkGroupId, name);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ScramblingApi#scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.ScramblingApi;

public class ScramblingApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ScramblingApi apiInstance = new ScramblingApi();
        String networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example; // String | Filter to get all EMMG in a NetworkGroup
        String name = name_example; // String | Filter to get EMMG by name
        try {
            array[EMMGConfiguration] result = apiInstance.scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration(networkGroupId, name);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ScramblingApi#scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
String *networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example; // Filter to get all EMMG in a NetworkGroup (optional)
String *name = name_example; // Filter to get EMMG by name (optional)

ScramblingApi *apiInstance = [[ScramblingApi alloc] init];

// Get all EMMG by filter criteria
[apiInstance scramblingGetAllEMMGConfigurationWith:networkGroupId
    name:name
              completionHandler: ^(array[EMMGConfiguration] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.ScramblingApi()

var opts = { 
  'networkGroupId': networkGroupId_example, // {String} Filter to get all EMMG in a NetworkGroup
  'name': name_example // {String} Filter to get EMMG by name
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class scramblingGetAllEMMGConfigurationExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            var apiInstance = new ScramblingApi();
            var networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example;  // String | Filter to get all EMMG in a NetworkGroup (optional) 
            var name = name_example;  // String | Filter to get EMMG by name (optional) 

            try
            {
                // Get all EMMG by filter criteria
                array[EMMGConfiguration] result = apiInstance.scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration(networkGroupId, name);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ScramblingApi.scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import swagger_client
from swagger_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# create an instance of the API class
api_instance = swagger_client.ScramblingApi()
networkGroupId = networkGroupId_example # String | Filter to get all EMMG in a NetworkGroup (optional)
name = name_example # String | Filter to get EMMG by name (optional)

try: 
    # Get all EMMG by filter criteria
    api_response = api_instance.scrambling_get_all_emmg_configuration(networkGroupId=networkGroupId, name=name)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling ScramblingApi->scramblingGetAllEMMGConfiguration: %s\n" % e)

namespace Example
{
    public class scramblingPatchScgByIdExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            var apiInstance = new ScramblingApi();
            var id = new UUID(); // UUID | Object ID of SCG
            var status = new ScgStatus(); // ScgStatus | SCG status to update

            try
            {
                // Scramble/Clear SCG by ID

                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ScramblingApi.scramblingPatchScgById: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

using System.Diagnostics;

using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class scramblingPutEMMByIdExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            var apiInstance = new ScramblingApi();
            var id = new UUID(); // UUID | Object ID of EMM stream
            var emmData = new EMMData(); // EMMData | EMM information to update

            try
            {
                // Update EMM stream by ID
                BaseCommand result = apiInstance.scramblingPutEMMById(id, emmData);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ScramblingApi.scramblingPutEMMById: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ServicesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ServicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        ServicesApi apiInstance = new ServicesApi();
        String proxySiteId = proxySiteId_example; // String | Query output services using given proxy site id
        try {
            array[ProxyServiceInfo] result = apiInstance.servicesGetAllOutputService(proxySiteId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ServicesApi#servicesGetAllOutputService");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.ServicesApi;

public class ServicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ServicesApi apiInstance = new ServicesApi();
        String proxySiteId = proxySiteId_example; // String | Query output services using given proxy site id
        try {
            array[ProxyServiceInfo] result = apiInstance.servicesGetAllOutputService(proxySiteId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ServicesApi#servicesGetAllOutputService");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
String *proxySiteId = proxySiteId_example; // Query output services using given proxy site id (optional)

ServicesApi *apiInstance = [[ServicesApi alloc] init];

// Get all Output Services
[apiInstance servicesGetAllOutputServiceWith:proxySiteId
              completionHandler: ^(array[ProxyServiceInfo] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.ServicesApi()

var opts = { 
  'proxySiteId': proxySiteId_example // {String} Query output services using given proxy site id
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.servicesGetAllOutputService(opts, callback);

servicesGetAllServicePlans

Get all Service Plans present on NMX server

Following is not supported: 1. Service Plan X 2. DvbT2 Transports


/api/Services/v2/ServicePlans

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET "https://127.0.0.1/api/Services/v2/ServicePlans?AllHierarchy=&ActiveOnly="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ServicesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ServicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        ServicesApi apiInstance = new ServicesApi();
        Boolean allHierarchy = true; // Boolean | If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans 
 If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details
        Boolean activeOnly = true; // Boolean | If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans 
 If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans
        try {
            array[ServicePlan] result = apiInstance.servicesGetAllServicePlans(allHierarchy, activeOnly);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ServicesApi#servicesGetAllServicePlans");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.ServicesApi;

public class ServicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ServicesApi apiInstance = new ServicesApi();
        Boolean allHierarchy = true; // Boolean | If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans 
 If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details
        Boolean activeOnly = true; // Boolean | If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans 
 If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans
        try {
            array[ServicePlan] result = apiInstance.servicesGetAllServicePlans(allHierarchy, activeOnly);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ServicesApi#servicesGetAllServicePlans");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
Boolean *allHierarchy = true; // If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans 
 If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details (optional)
Boolean *activeOnly = true; // If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans 
 If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans (optional)

ServicesApi *apiInstance = [[ServicesApi alloc] init];

// Get all Service Plans present on NMX server
[apiInstance servicesGetAllServicePlansWith:allHierarchy
    activeOnly:activeOnly
              completionHandler: ^(array[ServicePlan] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.ServicesApi()

var opts = { 
  'allHierarchy': true, // {Boolean} If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans 
 If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details
  'activeOnly': true // {Boolean} If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans 
 If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.servicesGetAllServicePlans(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class servicesGetAllServicePlansExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            var apiInstance = new ServicesApi();
            var allHierarchy = true;  // Boolean | If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans 
 If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details (optional) 
            var activeOnly = true;  // Boolean | If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans 
 If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans (optional) 

            try
            {
                // Get all Service Plans present on NMX server
                array[ServicePlan] result = apiInstance.servicesGetAllServicePlans(allHierarchy, activeOnly);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ServicesApi.servicesGetAllServicePlans: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

<?php
require_once(__DIR__ . '/vendor/autoload.php');

$api_instance = new Swagger\Client\Api\ServicesApi();
$allHierarchy = true; // Boolean | If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans 
 If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details
$activeOnly = true; // Boolean | If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans 
 If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans

try {
    $result = $api_instance->servicesGetAllServicePlans($allHierarchy, $activeOnly);
    print_r($result);
} catch (Exception $e) {
    echo 'Exception when calling ServicesApi->servicesGetAllServicePlans: ', $e->getMessage(), PHP_EOL;
}
?>
use Data::Dumper;
use WWW::SwaggerClient::Configuration;
use WWW::SwaggerClient::ServicesApi;

my $api_instance = WWW::SwaggerClient::ServicesApi->new();
my $allHierarchy = true; # Boolean | If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans 
 If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details
my $activeOnly = true; # Boolean | If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans 
 If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans

eval { 
    my $result = $api_instance->servicesGetAllServicePlans(allHierarchy => $allHierarchy, activeOnly => $activeOnly);
    print Dumper($result);
};
if ($@) {
    warn "Exception when calling ServicesApi->servicesGetAllServicePlans: $@\n";
}
from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import swagger_client
from swagger_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# create an instance of the API class
api_instance = swagger_client.ServicesApi()
allHierarchy = true # Boolean | If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans 
 If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details (optional)
activeOnly = true # Boolean | If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans 
 If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans (optional)

try: 
    # Get all Service Plans present on NMX server
    api_response = api_instance.services_get_all_service_plans(allHierarchy=allHierarchy, activeOnly=activeOnly)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling ServicesApi->servicesGetAllServicePlans: %s\n" % e)

Parameters

Query parameters
Name Description
AllHierarchy
Boolean
If AllHierarchy is false (default), response will only contain the list of Service Plans <br /> If AllHierarchy is true, response will contain list of Service Plans with full details
ActiveOnly
Boolean
If ActiveOnly is false (default), response will contain active and inactive Service Plans <br /> If ActiveOnly is true, response will contain only active Service Plans

Responses

Status: 200 - OK

  • Schema

Status: 401 - Unauthorized

Status: 503 - Service Unavailable

servicesGetDiviTrackPools

/api/Services/v2/DiviTrackPools

  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ServicesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ServicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        ServicesApi apiInstance = new ServicesApi();
        String networkGroupID = networkGroupID_example; // String | 
        String name = name_example; // String | 
        try {
            array[DiviTrackPoolInfo] result = apiInstance.servicesGetDiviTrackPools(networkGroupID, name);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ServicesApi#servicesGetDiviTrackPools");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.ServicesApi;

        }
    }
}
String *networkGroupID = networkGroupID_example; //  (optional)
String *name = name_example; //  (optional)

ServicesApi *apiInstance = [[ServicesApi alloc] init];

// Get list of all DiviTrack Pools
[apiInstance servicesGetDiviTrackPoolsWith:networkGroupID
    name:name
              completionHandler: ^(array[DiviTrackPoolInfo] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.ServicesApi()

var opts = { 
  'networkGroupID': networkGroupID_example, // {String} 
  'name': name_example // {String} 
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.servicesGetDiviTrackPools(opts, callback);

servicesPatchOutputTransports

Enable/Disable Output Transport by ID

Not allowed when NMX is added in Grid.<br /> For Master-Mirror transports :<br /> 1. In case of mirror transport, status can be updated only if master transport is enabled.<br /> 2. In case of master transport, If a master transport is enable/disabled then all of it's mirror transport will be enabled/disabled as well.


/api/Services/v2/OutputTransports/{id}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ServicesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ServicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        ServicesApi apiInstance = new ServicesApi();
        UUID id = ; // UUID | Output Transport ID
        String rebuildPsiMode = rebuildPsiMode_example; // String | RebuildPSI of Output Transport, default is ChangedOnly
        try {
            BaseCommand result = apiInstance.servicesPatchOutputTransportsForRebuildPsi(id, rebuildPsiMode);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ServicesApi#servicesPatchOutputTransportsForRebuildPsi");

servicesPutMWProfiles

Update properties of MW profile by ID

1. Not allowed when NMX is added in Grid 2. This API does not automatically update payload in profile property dependent descriptors. They must be updated manually by providing descriptor payload in request body. Example: For ISO 639 Language Descriptor (In an MW audio stream), payload depends upon the language set in profile. Hence, while updating Language in AudioTranscodingProperties, the descriptor should also be updated by providing descriptor payload in request body. 3. If the VideoProfile property of VideoTranscodingProperties value is set to "H.265 Main 10 (10-bit)" or set to another value from "H.265 Main 10 (10-bit)" then the API will update VideoProfile for all profiles.


/api/Services/v2/MWProfiles/{id}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ServicesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ServicesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        ServicesApi apiInstance = new ServicesApi();
        UUID id = ; // UUID | Object ID of MW Profile
        MWProfileInfo updateInfo = ; // MWProfileInfo | Payload for updating MW profile
        Boolean updateAllProfiles = true; // Boolean | Update properties in all profiles. Default: false
        try {
            BaseCommand result = apiInstance.servicesPutMWProfiles(id, updateInfo, updateAllProfiles);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ServicesApi#servicesPutMWProfiles");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

servicesPutOutputStream

Update Output stream by ID

1. Not allowed when NMX is added in Grid. 2. Updating the bitrate through this API is limited to broadcast output. For OTT output, user must use PUT /api/Services/v2/MWProfiles/{id} API.


/api/Services/v2/OutputStreams/{id}

servicesUpdateAlternateServiceActivation

/api/Services/v2/OutputServices/{id}/ActivateAlternateService

        try {
            BaseCommand result = apiInstance.servicesUpdateAlternateServiceActivation(id, activationInfo);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ServicesApi#servicesUpdateAlternateServiceActivation");
            e.printStackTrace();

    }

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.SuperServerApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class SuperServerApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        SuperServerApi apiInstance = new SuperServerApi();
        String gRSMode = gRSMode_example; // String | Filter the response by GRS Mode
        String name = name_example; // String | Filter the response by Name
        String iPAddress = iPAddress_example; // String | Filter the response by IP Address
        try {
            array[ProxySite] result = apiInstance.superServerGetAllProxySites(gRSMode, name, iPAddress);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling SuperServerApi#superServerGetAllProxySites");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.SuperServerApi;

public class SuperServerApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SuperServerApi apiInstance = new SuperServerApi();
        String gRSMode = gRSMode_example; // String | Filter the response by GRS Mode
        String name = name_example; // String | Filter the response by Name
        String iPAddress = iPAddress_example; // String | Filter the response by IP Address
        try {
            array[ProxySite] result = apiInstance.superServerGetAllProxySites(gRSMode, name, iPAddress);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling SuperServerApi#superServerGetAllProxySites");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
String *gRSMode = gRSMode_example; // Filter the response by GRS Mode (optional)
String *name = name_example; // Filter the response by Name (optional)
String *iPAddress = iPAddress_example; // Filter the response by IP Address (optional)

SuperServerApi *apiInstance = [[SuperServerApi alloc] init];

// Get all proxy sites
[apiInstance superServerGetAllProxySitesWith:gRSMode
    name:name
    iPAddress:iPAddress
              completionHandler: ^(array[ProxySite] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.SuperServerApi()

var opts = { 
  'gRSMode': gRSMode_example, // {String} Filter the response by GRS Mode
  'name': name_example, // {String} Filter the response by Name
  'iPAddress': iPAddress_example // {String} Filter the response by IP Address
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.superServerGetAllProxySites(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class superServerGetAllProxySitesExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            var apiInstance = new SuperServerApi();
            var gRSMode = gRSMode_example;  // String | Filter the response by GRS Mode (optional) 
            var name = name_example;  // String | Filter the response by Name (optional) 
            var iPAddress = iPAddress_example;  // String | Filter the response by IP Address (optional) 

            try
            {
                // Get all proxy sites
                array[ProxySite] result = apiInstance.superServerGetAllProxySites(gRSMode, name, iPAddress);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling SuperServerApi.superServerGetAllProxySites: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }

superServerUpdateProxySiteById

Update Properties of a Proxy Site its ID

Not allowed when NMX is added in Grid.

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.SuperServerApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class SuperServerApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        SuperServerApi apiInstance = new SuperServerApi();
        UUID id = ; // UUID | The object id of the remote site
        UpdateProxySite proxySite = ; // UpdateProxySite | Model to hold the editable properties
        try {
            Object result = apiInstance.superServerUpdateProxySiteById(id, proxySite);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling SuperServerApi#superServerUpdateProxySiteById");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.TimelineApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class TimelineApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        TimelineApi apiInstance = new TimelineApi();
        String scheduleState = scheduleState_example; // String | Optional filter to get batches by schedule state. Default: Scheduled
        String startTime = startTime_example; // String | The optional oldest Execution Time for Schedules (Format, yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.fff, Ex: 2018-04-22T05:38:51.457). Not applicable when scheduleState = Scheduled
        try {
            array[ScheduleInfo] result = apiInstance.timelineGetAllScheduledBatches(scheduleState, startTime);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling TimelineApi#timelineGetAllScheduledBatches");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.TimelineApi;

        TimelineApi apiInstance = new TimelineApi();

        String startTime = startTime_example; // String | The optional oldest Execution Time for Schedules (Format, yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.fff, Ex: 2018-04-22T05:38:51.457). Not applicable when scheduleState = Scheduled
        try {
            array[ScheduleInfo] result = apiInstance.timelineGetAllScheduledBatches(scheduleState, startTime);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling TimelineApi#timelineGetAllScheduledBatches");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
String *scheduleState = scheduleState_example; // Optional filter to get batches by schedule state. Default: Scheduled (optional)
String *startTime = startTime_example; // The optional oldest Execution Time for Schedules (Format, yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.fff, Ex: 2018-04-22T05:38:51.457). Not applicable when scheduleState = Scheduled (optional)

    startTime:startTime
              completionHandler: ^(array[ScheduleInfo] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

  'startTime': startTime_example // {String} The optional oldest Execution Time for Schedules (Format, yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.fff, Ex: 2018-04-22T05:38:51.457). Not applicable when scheduleState = Scheduled
};

  if (error) {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        TimelineApi apiInstance = new TimelineApi();
        String networkGroupID = networkGroupID_example; // String | Optional filter to get batches by network group id
        String servicePlanID = servicePlanID_example; // String | Optional filter to get batches by service plan id
        String name = name_example; // String | Optional filter to get batches by batch name
        try {
            array[BatchInfo] result = apiInstance.timelineGetAllStoredBatches(networkGroupID, servicePlanID, name);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling TimelineApi#timelineGetAllStoredBatches");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
import io.swagger.client.api.TimelineApi;

public class TimelineApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        TimelineApi apiInstance = new TimelineApi();
        String networkGroupID = networkGroupID_example; // String | Optional filter to get batches by network group id
        String servicePlanID = servicePlanID_example; // String | Optional filter to get batches by service plan id
        String name = name_example; // String | Optional filter to get batches by batch name
        try {
            array[BatchInfo] result = apiInstance.timelineGetAllStoredBatches(networkGroupID, servicePlanID, name);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling TimelineApi#timelineGetAllStoredBatches");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
String *networkGroupID = networkGroupID_example; // Optional filter to get batches by network group id (optional)
String *servicePlanID = servicePlanID_example; // Optional filter to get batches by service plan id (optional)
String *name = name_example; // Optional filter to get batches by batch name (optional)

TimelineApi *apiInstance = [[TimelineApi alloc] init];

// Get All Stored Batches
[apiInstance timelineGetAllStoredBatchesWith:networkGroupID
    servicePlanID:servicePlanID
    name:name
              completionHandler: ^(array[BatchInfo] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var NmxServerRestApi = require('nmx_server_rest_api');

var api = new NmxServerRestApi.TimelineApi()

var opts = { 
  'networkGroupID': networkGroupID_example, // {String} Optional filter to get batches by network group id
  'servicePlanID': servicePlanID_example, // {String} Optional filter to get batches by service plan id
  'name': name_example // {String} Optional filter to get batches by batch name
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.timelineGetAllStoredBatches(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class timelineGetAllStoredBatchesExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            var apiInstance = new TimelineApi();
            var networkGroupID = networkGroupID_example;  // String | Optional filter to get batches by network group id (optional) 
            var servicePlanID = servicePlanID_example;  // String | Optional filter to get batches by service plan id (optional) 
            var name = name_example;  // String | Optional filter to get batches by batch name (optional) 

            try
            {
                // Get All Stored Batches
                array[BatchInfo] result = apiInstance.timelineGetAllStoredBatches(networkGroupID, servicePlanID, name);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling TimelineApi.timelineGetAllStoredBatches: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

my $name = name_example; # String | Optional filter to get batches by batch name

    my $result = $api_instance->timelineGetAllStoredBatches(networkGroupID => $networkGroupID, servicePlanID => $servicePlanID, name => $name);

    warn "Exception when calling TimelineApi->timelineGetAllStoredBatches: $@\n";
}

from swagger_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

networkGroupID = networkGroupID_example # String | Optional filter to get batches by network group id (optional)
servicePlanID = servicePlanID_example # String | Optional filter to get batches by service plan id (optional)
name = name_example # String | Optional filter to get batches by batch name (optional)

try: 
    # Get All Stored Batches
    api_response = api_instance.timeline_get_all_stored_batches(networkGroupID=networkGroupID, servicePlanID=servicePlanID, name=name)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling TimelineApi->timelineGetAllStoredBatches: %s\n" % e)

            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
